Adds a new route before the wildcard route to prevent that we always redirect to the wildcard route.

For example, starting point:

```
const routes = [
  { path: '**', component: AppComponent }
];
```

Before:

```ts
const routes = [
  { path: '**', component: AppComponent },
  { path: 'foo', component: FooComponent }
];
```

After:

```ts
const routes = [
  { path: 'foo', component: FooComponent },
  { path: '**', component: AppComponent }
];
```


